This paper deals with quantitative information flow (QIF) and leakage functions, which are commonly studied in the field of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves the use of mathematical models and algorithms, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the efficiency of adaptive and non-adaptive strategies, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
